  + [purpose] is measure finite Euler-product and logarithmic-derivative residual behavior as sigma decreases toward 1 from above
  + [not_purpose] is RH proof, disproof, critical-line inspection, independent zero certification, or analytic-continuation authority

  = must: require all sigma values to be greater than 1
  = must: expose distance_to_sigma_1 for each sampled row
  = must: compare finite Euler-product and logarithmic-derivative residuals across sigma values and prime bounds
  = must: expose transition ratios for adjacent sigma values when residuals are nonzero
  = must: treat t values as fixed horizontal lines in the convergent half-plane
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_sigma_boundary_probe_not_critical_line_evidence
  - never: treat approach toward sigma = 1 as crossing into the critical strip
  - never: claim RH proof, disproof, zero certification, or critical-line behavior from finite sigma-boundary traces

